Defendant Charles C Shouse in court with attorney Craig Michael Kuhary.   appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1 and 4.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts 2, 3, and 5 are dismissed and read in.  Count #6 dismissed by operation of law.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

Count #1:

6 MONTHS JAIL;

*D/L REVOCATION: 18 months.
*IGNITION INTERLOCK: 18 months.

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling.
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Attend Victim Impact Panel;
*Not to operate a motor vehicle unless properly licensed;
*Perform 50 hours community service @ a rate of $10.00 per hour to be applied to costs and fines;

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation - to be forward to Waukesha County Sheriff's  Department);

FINE:  $1229.00 (apply cash bail to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE: $200.00 (to be paid as a conditional of probation);

CONDITION TIME:  60 DAYS  NON WORKING HOURS w/Standard Release Conditions, Defendant to report no later than 7:00 p.m. on Friday, October 30, 2015.. 

COUNT #4:
IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

4 MONTHS JAIL; (consecutive to Count #1)

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION: SEE COUNT 1

COSTS: $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
DNA SURCHARGE: $200.00 to be paid as a condition of probation)
CONDITION TIME:  30 Days non-working hours, (STAYED), to be used at the agent's discretion;
